        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 3:33PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Porter, or over Chesterton, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chesterton, Porter, Dune Acres, Burns Harbor, Ogden Dunes, Beverly
Shores, Portage, and Town of Pines.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
